column5: keepin it short and sweet. took the pin out again today. water was high fast and pretty stirred up but i still managed to get 2. the second one being a complete tank and my new pb    new pb
Gorgeous fat tank! Way to go.
Nice fish. That things a monster.
haha thanks guys, my jaw dropped when i saw the size of her
WOW! RIVERMONSTER! lol  How was the fight? other fish is nice too btw.
Wow, the pic on this post is way more impressive than when I saw it on your camera!  That may be the biggest one I have seen posted this fall.  Well Done  Clarence

10-15 minutes, had me in a whole bunch of trouble bringing me into the rocks i thought for sure she was gonna break me off. but i managed to hike down shore a bit get the line off the rocks to continue the fight then a friend of mine netted her for me when she came in close
wow- nice fish
Beautiful fish! Glad to see you taped your reel in place.
nice fish bud:thumbsup_anim:
Awesome.  Gotta love teamwork
nice fish !! congrats on the new PB !!!!
That thing looks like a mutant....HUGE!!!!  Nicely done....good day to bring the net
Congrats on both of those fish. thank goodness for a net.
You should mail that fish to The Biggest Loser for the next season's cast!
That's a huge bullet! nice work.
thats a sow if i ever saw one, im just a tid bit jealous haha but thanks for the motivation!
That is a beautiful fish!
Wow, that's a great fish and a great photo to remember 'er by!  Nice job, Miller.
Very fat fish! Congrats on the PB!
BEAUTE!
